cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY

This paper discusses the availability of research data over time, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper focuses on the preservation and sharing of research data. The paper also touches on information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CR), as data sharing policies can impact these areas. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for data management (cs.DB) and the ethical considerations surrounding data sharing (cs.CY).
